Introduction to the Blockchain
------------------------------

Short description
-----------------

Since 2012 we've been reading about how crytpocurrencies are the new
internet, and have heard every opinion from positive to skeptical to
vehemently against. How do cryptocurrencies actually work though? What
technologies and principles are they based on? This talk will
introduce the audience to the blockchain: a <definition of block chain
here>. We'll cover what a blockchain is, how it works, the cool math
and logic that it uses, and discuss some uses of the blockchain beyond
just cryptocurrencies. This will explain the nuts and bolts of
blockchains

